                                 forward, bearded, with puffed hair, dressed in a chiton and
                                 chlamys, wearing a pendilia crown surmounted by a small cross,
                                 holding the cruciferous globe in his right hand and the akakia in
                                 his left. In the lower field, on either side of the effigy, on the
                                 left is the letter Γ, with the crosier turned to the left, i.e. .
                                 On the right, a shape similar to an I.</figDesc>
